pullRequest.body:
We introduce whiskering operators. This allows us to introduce a simp-normal form for morphisms in monoidal categories. Rewriting into simp-normal forms is especially useful when combined with the coherence tactic.

I'm happy to use this technique for multiline proofs needed in a calc block, however.

Can you make a separate PR with these precedence changes, so that it's clear what the fallout is?

I canceled the change of precedence. Setting `79`, which is lower than `80` for the usual composition `≫`, only affects one pair of parenthesis in https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6307/commits/c1bce84c5ba2714d3215f03485a3f410211fef0a. Now I don't think we really need to set a lower precedence here.
https://github.com/leanprover/std4/pull/269 will make it so you don't have to add all these
Maybe there aren't very many of them, but lemmas like these might be worth extracting to a standalone PR so that they're not held hostage by the merge conflicts.
I made a standalone PR for such lemmas: #8191.

These now exist!

```suggestion
abbrev LaxMonoidal.ofTensorHom (F : C → D) [Functorial.{v₁, v₂} F] [LaxMonoidalStruct F]
```
since otherwise this isn't reducibly defeq to its argument.
Is this refactor something that could be split out separately?

@eric-wieser I noticed that `LaxMonoidalStruct` is essentially only used in `LaxMonoidal.ofTensorHom`, which is another constructor for `LaxMonoidal` using `tenroHom` instead of the whiskerings, to avoid tautological transport for `ε` and `μ`. I now think we don't need this type class at this point because it has a tiny benefit, so I have reverted the addition of this type class for now.
Temporary in what sense?
I intended this lemma would be replaced by whiskering version (`coevaluation_evaluation`) in the future after refactoring proofs in this file.
I attempted such a refactoring in #8265.
